cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper presents a visual tracking algorithm based on a multi-domain convolutional neural network (MDNet), which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces novel loss terms to differentiate foreground instances across multiple domains and learn a more discriminative embedding of target objects with similar semantics, which involves ML techniques such as deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely. Additionally, the paper involves techniques for enhancing representation quality and maintaining high-resolution feature maps, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on multiple tracking benchmark datasets, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
